2026 Regular Session
HOUSE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 88
BY REPRESENTATIVE MILLER
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH: Recognizes April 28, 2026, as Nurses Day and May 6
through May 12, 2026, as National Nurses Week in Louisiana
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To recognize April 28, 2026, as Nurses Day and May 6 through May 12, 2026, as National
3 Nurses Week in Louisiana.
4 WHEREAS, the "Power of Nurses" is the theme for Nurses Day at the Capitol; and
5 WHEREAS, over sixty-six thousand registered nurses, including over ten thousand
6 advanced practice registered nurses, are actively licensed in Louisiana; and
7 WHEREAS, the Louisiana State Nurses Association is a leading voice for healthcare
8 advocacy in the state for nurses, healthcare settings, and citizens; and
9 WHEREAS, the Louisiana State Nurses Association has established an expanding
10 program of advocacy that collaborates with other professional organizations and solicits
11 input from nurses statewide; and
12 WHEREAS, the Louisiana State Nurses Association promotes ethical care and high
13 standards for the practice of professional nursing; and
14 WHEREAS, the Louisiana State Nurses Association advocates for the inclusion of
15 registered nurses on decision making boards and commissions; and
16 WHEREAS, the Louisiana State Nurses Association advocates for increasing access
17 to primary and preventive healthcare; and
18 WHEREAS, the Louisiana State Nurses Association advocates for access to quality
19 maternal-child healthcare; and
20 WHEREAS, the Louisiana State Nurses Association advocates for access to quality
21 mental healthcare; and
