1 WHEREAS, the Louisiana State Nurses Association advocates for a safe work
2 environment that promotes the wellbeing of nurses; and
3 WHEREAS, the Louisiana State Nurses Association supports the American Nurses
4 Association's Nursing Code of Ethics, which calls upon nurses to "respect the inherent
5 dignity, worth, unique attributes, and human rights of all individuals"; and
6 WHEREAS, the Louisiana State Nurses Association advocates for support for
7 nursing workforce development to create a sustainable healthcare workforce; and
8 WHEREAS, registered nurses are well-suited to address the diverse and emerging
9 healthcare needs of the population in a wide range of settings; and
10 WHEREAS, registered nurses make a difference by influencing and shaping health
11 policy decisions that ensure all Louisiana residents have access to safe, high-quality,
12 affordable healthcare coverage.
13 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
14 declare April 28, 2026, as Nurses Day at the State Capitol and May 6 through May 12, 2026,
15 as National Nurses Week in Louisiana.
